Verse: And some of the people of Levi spoke to the people. Those people of Levi were Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah, Hodiah, Shebaniah and Pethahiah.  Those people of Levi said, ["You(people) (imp) stand-up]. And you(people) (imp) praise your(Israelites') God Yahweh. Yahweh always lived. And Yahweh will live forever." Then (implicit) those people prayed to Yahweh. Those people prayed, ["Yahweh _implicit, we(people) praise the wonderful/glorious name of you(Yahweh)]. Those (alt) people prayed, ["Yahweh [who is _gnomic wonderful/glorious], we(people) praise you(Yahweh)]. We(Israelites) pray-hope [that our(Yahweh's) name will become great/exalted].
